![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/6e27d2c1-5b8f-4378-9ff6-0ec62d34bc5c/20240517_083736.jpg?format=original)

According to the Wrestling Observer Newsletter, Eddie Kingston suffered a devastating injury during the New Japan show in Ontario, California on May 11. Initially believed to have broken his leg, further examination on May 13 confirmed the diagnosis.

As a result, All Elite Wrestling (AEW) was forced to make significant changes to their upcoming events. The main event for AEW Dynamite was altered, and the highly anticipated AEW Double or Nothing main event was also changed due to Kingston's injury.

In a swift move, AEW brought in Darby Allin to replace Kingston in the affected matches. Allin, known for his high-flying and hard-hitting style, is expected to bring a new dynamic to the altered matchups.

Kingston, known for his intense and physical in-ring style, is expected to undergo treatment and rehabilitation for his broken leg. Fans and fellow wrestlers have been sending well wishes and support for a speedy recovery.

The changes to AEW Dynamite and Double or Nothing main events have not been officially announced, but fans are eagerly awaiting the new matchups and storylines that will unfold in the coming weeks.